mcqs.question:
Consider the following OpenMP code:

int x = 5;
#pragma omp parallel num_threads(4)
{
    x = x + 1;
}
printf("%d\n", x);

What is the output and why?

Given the code below, which variable(s) require explicit data-sharing attribute specification when using '#pragma omp parallel default(none)'?

int a = 10;
float b = 3.14;
int main() {
    int c = 5;
    #pragma omp parallel default(none) private(c)
    {
        int d = a + c; // uses a, c
        b = b + 1.0;   // uses b
    }
}

What is the final value of 'sum' after executing this OpenMP code with 4 threads?

int sum = 0;
#pragma omp parallel for reduction(+:sum)
for (int i = 1; i <= 100; i++) {
    sum += i;
}

In the following code, what will be printed for variable 'i' after the parallel region?

int i = 100;
#pragma omp parallel for private(i)
for (i = 0; i < 4; i++) {
    // Each thread has its own copy of i
}
printf("i = %d\n", i);

Analyze this code and identify the race condition:

int counter = 0;
#pragma omp parallel num_threads(8)
{
    // Each thread increments counter 1000 times
    for (int j = 0; j < 1000; j++)
        counter++;
}
printf("Counter: %d\n", counter);

What is the actual value of counter most likely to be?

Given the following code with '#pragma omp parallel for lastprivate(x)', what value is printed?

int x = 1;
#pragma omp parallel for lastprivate(x)
for (int i = 1; i <= 4; i++) {
    x = i * 2;
}
printf("x = %d\n", x);

Consider this code with '#pragma omp single'. Which variables are guaranteed to have consistent values across all threads after the construct?

int a = 5;
#pragma omp parallel
{
    #pragma omp single
    {
        a = 10;
    }
    // Value of 'a' here?
}

Which clause should be used to fix this code to correctly compute the product?

double result = 1.0;
#pragma omp parallel for
for (int i = 1; i <= 10; i++) {
    result *= i;
}
